data.name: Bloodbond March
data.oracle_text: Whenever a player casts a creature spell, each player returns all cards with the same name as that spell from his or her graveyard to the battlefield.
data.flavor_text: The Golgari support a vast army because death never ends its soldiers' service.

data.name: Dark Heart of the Wood
data.oracle_text: Sacrifice a Forest: You gain 3 life.
data.flavor_text:
"The soil here is rich with the rotting dead, and the sun's fingers barely penetrate the dark canopy. Plant our brethren here. This shall be our sanctuary."
—Savra

data.name: Drooling Groodion
data.oracle_text: {2}{B}{G}, Sacrifice a creature: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn. Another target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.
data.flavor_text:
"The Golgari expand, yes, but I refuse to call their tainted creations 'growth.'"
—Veszka, Selesnya evangel

data.name: Gaze of the Gorgon
data.oracle_text:
({B/G} can be paid with either {B} or {G}.)
Regenerate target creature. At this turn's next end of combat, destroy all creatures that blocked or were blocked by it this turn.
data.flavor_text: Even the dead give way to the mineral gaze of the gorgon.

data.name: Gleancrawler
data.oracle_text:
({B/G} can be paid with either {B} or {G}.)
Trample
At the beginning of your end step, return to your hand all creature cards in your graveyard that were put there from the battlefield this turn.

data.name: Golgari Germination
data.oracle_text: Whenever a nontoken creature you control dies, create a 1/1 green Saproling creature token.
data.flavor_text: The Golgari don't bury their dead. They plant them.

data.name: Golgari Guildmage
data.oracle_text:
{4}{B}, Sacrifice a creature: Return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
{4}{G}: Put a +1/+1 counter on target creature.

data.name: Golgari Rotwurm
data.oracle_text: {B}, Sacrifice a creature: Target player loses 1 life.
data.flavor_text: Like corpse-worms through a carapace, rotwurms slide through the hollowed bones of the undercity.

data.name: Grave-Shell Scarab
data.oracle_text:
{1}, Sacrifice Grave-Shell Scarab: Draw a card.
Dredge 1 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly one card from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

data.name: Putrefy
data.oracle_text: Destroy target artifact or creature. It can't be regenerated.
data.flavor_text:
"All matter, animate or not, rots when exposed to time. We merely speed up the process."
—Ezoc, Golgari rot farmer

data.name: Savra, Queen of the Golgari
data.oracle_text:
Whenever you sacrifice a black creature, you may pay 2 life. If you do, each other player sacrifices a creature.
Whenever you sacrifice a green creature, you may gain 2 life.
data.flavor_text: "Nature's most raw beauty is the circle: perfect in its continuance, with no break between death and life."

data.name: Shambling Shell
data.oracle_text:
Sacrifice Shambling Shell: Put a +1/+1 counter on target creature.
Dredge 3 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly three cards from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

data.name: Sisters of Stone Death
data.oracle_text:
{G}: Target creature blocks Sisters of Stone Death this turn if able.
{B}{G}: Exile target creature blocking or blocked by Sisters of Stone Death.
{2}{B}: Put a creature card exiled with Sisters of Stone Death onto the battlefield under your control.

data.name: Vulturous Zombie
data.oracle_text:
Flying
Whenever a card is put into an opponent's graveyard from anywhere, put a +1/+1 counter on Vulturous Zombie.
data.flavor_text:
"When something dies, all things benefit. Well okay, just our things."
—Ezoc, Golgari rot farmer

data.name: Woodwraith Corrupter
data.oracle_text: {1}{B}{G}, {T}: Target Forest becomes a 4/4 black and green Elemental Horror creature. It's still a land.
data.flavor_text:
"Its darkened sap penetrates natural fibers and spreads its own genes. Emulation experiments are underway."
—Simic research notes

data.name: Woodwraith Strangler
data.oracle_text: Exile a creature card from your graveyard: Regenerate Woodwraith Strangler.
data.flavor_text:
"Nothing could be more natural than roots sucking nourishment from the dead."
—Savra
